## O CIRCLE COLOR RULE

The O circle stroke is **not always white/silver**. Its color depends on whether either digit is 0:

| Situation | O circle color |
|-----------|---------------|
| Neither digit is 0 (e.g. 36, 13, 27) | **White/silver** — neutral, both digits have their own markers |
| Second digit is 0 (e.g. 10, 20, 30) | **Electric teal** — O carries the second digit (0) in teal |
| First digit is 0 (e.g. 01–09, single digits) | **Neon-blue** — O carries the first digit (0) in blue |
| Both digits are 0 (00) | O split: half blue, half teal — or a two-tone glow ring |

