> **Total dash length = exactly ½ the radius of the O circle.**  
> - One half of the dash length lies **inside** the O  
> - One half of the dash length lies **outside** the O  
> The circle's stroke precisely bisects every dash at its exact midpoint.

**Additional mandatory rules:**
- Dash thickness = **always exactly 2×** the stroke thickness of the O circle
- Dash orientation = radial (perfectly aligned with the radius at the crossing point)
- Consistent dash length and thickness across all glyphs
- Dashes must clearly pierce the ring — never fully inside or fully outside
